Global Vapour Barrier Films Market Insights
Vapour Barrier Films Market size was valued at USD 2.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 4.1 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.3% from 2024 to 2030.

Vapour Barrier Films Market Overview
The global vapour barrier films market is poised for significant growth, valued at USD 7.7 billion in 2024 and expected to reach USD 11.5 billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.2% during the forecast period. The increasing demand for moisture control solutions in construction, packaging, and other industrial sectors is driving market expansion. The market benefits from innovations in material science, with manufacturers introducing advanced barrier films that provide higher durability and performance. These films are crucial in preventing the movement of water vapour, thus protecting structures from mould growth and decay. The rise in construction activities, particularly in residential and commercial buildings, continues to support market growth.

